{"article_id":"5TzFKsq4xbn1kDkW","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"President Obama on Thursday downplayed the prospect of any imminent U.S. airstrikes in Syria ,","depth":4},{"id":1,"text":"saying","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"`` we do n't have a strategy yet ''","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"and stressing","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"that military advisers are still reviewing options","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"for confronting Islamic State militants .","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"At the same time , the president bluntly ruled out U.S. military action","depth":5},{"id":7,"text":"for dealing with another international crisis","depth":6},{"id":8,"text":"-- mounting evidence of Russian incursions into eastern Ukraine .","depth":6},{"id":9,"text":"`` We are not taking military action","depth":6},{"id":10,"text":"to solve the Ukrainian problem , ''","depth":6},{"id":11,"text":"Obama said .","depth":5},{"id":12,"text":"The president addressed both crises during remarks in the White House briefing room late Thursday afternoon ,","depth":3},{"id":13,"text":"as Congress prepares to return from the summer recess .","depth":3},{"id":14,"text":"In recent days , lawmakers on both sides of the aisle have demanded","depth":5},{"id":15,"text":"that the U.S. strategy","depth":7},{"id":16,"text":"for targeting the Islamic State","depth":7},{"id":17,"text":"be put to a vote on Capitol Hill , amid speculation","depth":7},{"id":18,"text":"the military campaign might expand into Syria .","depth":7},{"id":19,"text":"But Obama stressed Thursday","depth":7},{"id":20,"text":"that `` we do n't have a strategy yet ''","depth":7},{"id":21,"text":"and pushed back on reports","depth":7},{"id":22,"text":"that ,","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"he said ,","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"suggest","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"the country is about to go `` full scale on an elaborate strategy '' in the Middle East .","depth":8},{"id":26,"text":"`` The suggestion ,","depth":10},{"id":27,"text":"I guess ,","depth":10},{"id":28,"text":"has been that we 'll start moving forward imminently","depth":9},{"id":29,"text":"and somehow Congress , still out of town , is going to be left in the dark , ''","depth":8},{"id":30,"text":"he said .","depth":7},{"id":31,"text":"`` That 's not what 's going to happen . ''","depth":6},{"id":32,"text":"White House Press Secretary Josh Earnest later clarified on CNN","depth":5},{"id":33,"text":"that the president referred specifically to Syria","depth":6},{"id":34,"text":"when he said","depth":7},{"id":35,"text":"there was no strategy yet .","depth":7},{"id":36,"text":"Obama indicated","depth":8},{"id":37,"text":"that for the time being , the U.S. will continue to conduct airstrikes in northern Iraq and humanitarian missions ,","depth":8},{"id":38,"text":"while working politically and diplomatically","depth":8},{"id":39,"text":"to `` cobble together '' a coalition for whatever the long-term strategy is .","depth":8},{"id":40,"text":"To that end , he said","depth":7},{"id":41,"text":"he is sending Secretary of State John Kerry to the region","depth":8},{"id":42,"text":"to build a `` coalition ''","depth":9},{"id":43,"text":"to confront the threat .","depth":9},{"id":44,"text":"Reports about a potential expanded military campaign follow calls by some lawmakers","depth":7},{"id":45,"text":"to strike the Islamic State ,","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"also known as ISIS or ISIL ,","depth":9},{"id":47,"text":"in Syria as well as Iraq .","depth":8},{"id":48,"text":"Military leaders have also said","depth":7},{"id":49,"text":"the organization will have to be dealt with in some way on the Syrian side of the border .","depth":7},{"id":50,"text":"Obama acknowledged Thursday","depth":6},{"id":51,"text":"that he 's directed military leaders","depth":7},{"id":52,"text":"to prepare a `` range of options '' on ISIS .","depth":7},{"id":53,"text":"He was heading next into a National Security Council meeting","depth":6},{"id":54,"text":"where he was expected to discuss the strategy with advisers .","depth":6},{"id":55,"text":"`` ISIL poses an immediate threat to the people of Iraq and the people of the region , ''","depth":8},{"id":56,"text":"Obama said ,","depth":8},{"id":57,"text":"while calling for a `` broader , comprehensive strategy . ''","depth":7},{"id":58,"text":"But he said","depth":8},{"id":59,"text":"he does n't want to `` put the cart before the horse . ''","depth":8},{"id":60,"text":"The president said ,","depth":8},{"id":61,"text":"once a strategy is formed ,","depth":10},{"id":62,"text":"there `` will be a military aspect to that ''","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"and might be a role for an `` international coalition ''","depth":10},{"id":64,"text":"providing air support .","depth":10},{"id":65,"text":"But he was vague on the question","depth":7},{"id":66,"text":"of what to do in Syria .","depth":7},{"id":67,"text":"Amid speculation","depth":9},{"id":68,"text":"over whether the U.S. would ever partner with Bashar Assad","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"to fight ISIS on that side of the border ,","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"Obama reiterated his view","depth":9},{"id":71,"text":"that `` Assad 's lost legitimacy . ''","depth":9},{"id":72,"text":"He said","depth":8},{"id":73,"text":"the U.S. would continue to support the `` moderate opposition '' in the country ,","depth":9},{"id":74,"text":"giving people a choice other than just Assad or ISIS .","depth":9},{"id":75,"text":"Senate Republican Leader Mitch McConnell , after Obama 's remarks , urged the president to develop a `` regional strategy '' for the Islamic State","depth":8},{"id":76,"text":"and present it to Congress and the American people .","depth":8},{"id":77,"text":"`` If the President is prepared to engage Congress with a strategic plan","depth":10},{"id":78,"text":"to protect the U.S. and our allies from ISIL ,","depth":10},{"id":79,"text":"I believe","depth":10},{"id":80,"text":"he will have significant congressional support , ''","depth":10},{"id":81,"text":"he said .","depth":8},{"id":82,"text":"`` But do n't forget ,","depth":7},{"id":83,"text":"the threat from ISIL is real","depth":9},{"id":84,"text":"and it 's growing","depth":9},{"id":85,"text":"-- and it is time","depth":10},{"id":86,"text":"for President Obama to exercise some leadership","depth":10},{"id":87,"text":"in launching a response . ''","depth":9},{"id":88,"text":"The president 's remarks also came amid increased tensions between Russia and Ukraine .","depth":7},{"id":89,"text":"Officials in Ukraine say","depth":8},{"id":90,"text":"two Russian military columns rolled into the southeastern part of the country","depth":9},{"id":91,"text":"after missiles were fired at a border post .","depth":9},{"id":92,"text":"Obama on Thursday blamed Russia for the unrest ,","depth":9},{"id":93,"text":"saying","depth":10},{"id":94,"text":"the country deliberately and repeatedly has violated Ukraine 's sovereignty .","depth":10},{"id":95,"text":"He said","depth":9},{"id":96,"text":"Russia is training , arming and funding pro-Russian separatists in Russia .","depth":9},{"id":97,"text":"Obama , though , said","depth":10},{"id":98,"text":"a `` military solution to this problem is not going to be forthcoming . ''","depth":10},{"id":99,"text":"Rather ,","depth":10},{"id":100,"text":"he said","depth":11},{"id":101,"text":"he wants to continue to mobilize the international community","depth":12},{"id":102,"text":"to bring pressure on Russia .","depth":12},{"id":103,"text":"`` This ongoing Russian incursion into Ukraine will only bring more costs and consequences for Russia , ''","depth":9},{"id":104,"text":"Obama said .","depth":9},{"id":105,"text":"Obama said","depth":8},{"id":106,"text":"Ukrainian President Petro Poroshenko will visit the White House next month , in what would be his first visit","depth":9},{"id":107,"text":"since becoming president .","depth":9},{"id":108,"text":"Obama said","depth":8},{"id":109,"text":"he also spoke by phone Thursday with German Chancellor Angela Merkel .","depth":8},{"id":110,"text":"In a written statement , though , Sens . John McCain , R-Ariz. , and Lindsey Graham , R-S.C. , said","depth":8},{"id":111,"text":"Russia 's actions can only be described as a `` cross-border military invasion , ''","depth":9},{"id":112,"text":"adding :","depth":10},{"id":113,"text":"`` To claim it is anything other than that is to inhabit President Putin 's Orwellian universe . ''","depth":10},{"id":114,"text":"They urged broader `` sectoral '' sanctions and U.S. and European military support for Ukraine .","depth":8},{"id":115,"text":"`` This is a moment","depth":11},{"id":116,"text":"to speak","depth":12},{"id":117,"text":"and act with clarity .","depth":12},{"id":118,"text":"A sovereign nation in the heart of Europe is being invaded by its larger neighbor , ''","depth":11},{"id":119,"text":"they said .","depth":11},{"id":120,"text":"`` If we will not or can not defend our own values now , as well as friends","depth":11},{"id":121,"text":"who share them ,","depth":11},{"id":122,"text":"the future will be dark and dangerous indeed , not just for Ukraine","depth":11},{"id":123,"text":"but for us too . ''","depth":11},{"id":124,"text":"At the end of Thursday 's remarks , Obama briefly addressed ongoing deliberations over possible executive action on immigration .","depth":7},{"id":125,"text":"Republicans have voiced concern","depth":8},{"id":126,"text":"he 'll issue a mass reprieve in the coming weeks for illegal immigrants .","depth":8},{"id":127,"text":"Obama did not indicate","depth":8},{"id":128,"text":"what he might decide","depth":8},{"id":129,"text":"but said :","depth":8},{"id":130,"text":"`` In the absence of congressional action , I 'm going to do what I can","depth":9},{"id":131,"text":"to make sure the system works better . ''","depth":9}],"relations":[{"parent":263,"left":145,"right":262,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":145,"left":143,"right":144,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":14